Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.90,0:00:21.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so as always, keep this as a starting point
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.13,0:00:24.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which hopefully you have on some CodePen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.03,0:00:25.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or somewhere on your computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.93,0:00:30.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if not, the link to this code will be in this lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.03,0:00:33.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what I want you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.06,0:00:36.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is basically to change this to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.42,0:00:41.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And essentially there are only two big changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.41,0:00:44.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, we have this sale label here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.25,0:00:48.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in this top left corner of the element.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.09,0:00:50.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then also down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.09,0:00:54.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we have basically these six available colors
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.08,0:00:56.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in which we can buy the shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:01:00.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to build this part here and this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:03.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this sale is very similar
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.57,0:01:05.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to something that we did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.66,0:01:10.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So hopefully you remember that's this, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.78,0:01:13.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in this case, you actually don't need to use
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.61,0:01:16.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a pseudo element for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.11,0:01:19.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can simply add a element, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.19,0:01:23.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a paragraph for the sale and then position it here,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.56,0:01:27.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,just like we did it in one of the previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:30.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, maybe you're noticing this detail
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.09,0:01:33.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that in this text, there is some space
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.26,0:01:35.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,between the different characters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.53,0:01:38.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or these letters here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so there is a CSS property which allows you to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.33,0:01:45.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what I want you to do is to Google that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.53,0:01:48.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to use Google to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:51.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,how you can add that space a little bit like I showed you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.81,0:01:56.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in the developer skills lecture about Googling.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.36,0:01:59.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now you can apply that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:00.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.77,0:02:03.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that is one of the things that you need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.40,0:02:06.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the other one is this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.25,0:02:07.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically what you will need
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.83,0:02:10.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to do is to create an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.66,0:02:14.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then inside of that element, which can be a simple div.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.38,0:02:17.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So inside of that element,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then you need to create six more elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:23.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And these can also be divs if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.26,0:02:25.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then all you need to do is to give each of them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.97,0:02:28.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a color and put them side by side,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:31.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,using a neat little trick
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.11,0:02:35.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that we actually also learned in one of the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:37.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And in particular, it was the lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.40,0:02:42.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,about the types of boxes, if I remember correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:46.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this was a nice little trick that we used there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:48.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so you can use that here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.67,0:02:50.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if you don't remember it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.61,0:02:53.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as always there is absolutely no problem
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.64,0:02:56.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you need to go back to our code
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.06,0:02:58.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and look up exactly how we did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.88,0:03:02.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the same, of course, goes for this technique here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.13,0:03:04.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't expect that you memorize
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.30,0:03:06.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all the techniques that I show you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:09.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you can look them up in your code
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.05,0:03:11.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and translate them to a different situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.78,0:03:15.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that already would be an amazing achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:16.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.22,0:03:18.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So if you can just do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.03,0:03:21.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then please go ahead and pause the video now
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:23.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll see you once you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:29.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right back to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.75,0:03:33.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And let's start with the sale label.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:37.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So as I said, I will simply add a paragraph somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.52,0:03:40.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And since we will position it, absolutely,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.85,0:03:43.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't really matter where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.33,0:03:45.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I will just put it here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.06,0:03:47.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,close to the price and the shipping
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.30,0:03:49.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because semantically that's where
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.81,0:03:51.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it makes sense to be located.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.93,0:03:58.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's give it a class of sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.04,0:04:04.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then we want the text of sale as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.69,0:04:07.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then let's close this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:11.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now we're here in our CSS.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.82,0:04:16.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put it also close to this shipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.97,0:04:17.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:22.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And let's start by adding some visual styles to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.67,0:04:28.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So some background color, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:30.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And here you could have just used
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:32.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,any red color that you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.44,0:04:35.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For example, using the VS Code Color Picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.57,0:04:37.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I also did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:40.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so the color I came up with is ec2f2f.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:45.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:47.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It actually go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.24,0:04:49.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.37,0:04:53.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's worry about the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.01,0:04:55.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's make it white.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.09,0:04:57.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.81,0:05:03.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a font size of 12 pixels and make it uppercase.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:11.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And make it bold as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:16.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So font weight, bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:21.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give it some padding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.06,0:05:24.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,7 pixels at the top, 15 left and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.15,0:05:27.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And again, these don't really matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:29.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But many times it's a good idea
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:31.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to have the horizontal padding
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:34.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to be kind of double of vertical.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:36.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good rule of thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.58,0:05:38.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that many times looks very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:44.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now the next step is that, actually we want this element
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.30,0:05:47.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,only to occupy the space that it actually needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.48,0:05:51.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, there are two techniques for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.85,0:05:54.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually just one, but you could also kind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.77,0:05:57.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of achieve this in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:59.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the best way to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:04.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,would be to set a display to inline box,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.51,0:06:08.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,actually inline block.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:12.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so now indeed, just like any inline element,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.29,0:06:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the box only occupies the space of its content.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.44,0:06:18.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:20.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the correct solution,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.03,0:06:23.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but let's comment this out to show you another solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.84,0:06:26.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you could have also kind of guessed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.06,0:06:29.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the with of this element, if you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.63,0:06:33.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say 100 pixels and then we could adjust it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.93,0:06:39.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's say just 80 pixels or just 50 pixels maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.25,0:06:42.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or 40 even.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.74,0:06:45.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then once you kind of got close,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.78,0:06:49.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you can then just say text, align, center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.90,0:06:54.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because now there is actually enough space
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.37,0:06:56.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,around the element inside
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.07,0:06:58.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of which the text could then be centered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:00.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.17,0:07:02.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So when we have actually a width,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:04.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then we are no longer in that situation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:08.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where text align center doesn't make sense in an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:12.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like we had before here with these links.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.12,0:07:14.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that? So I think like two lectures ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.35,0:07:19.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But anyway, this is not the preferred solution,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.67,0:07:23.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it is something that we could also have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.30,0:07:27.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, I found that interesting to also show you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.37,0:07:29.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so now it's time to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:33.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,absolutely position this element right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.62,0:07:37.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's remember that the first thing that we need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:40.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in order to absolutely position an element
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:44.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is to define in relation to what parent element,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.33,0:07:46.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,this element should be positioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.66,0:07:50.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so on that parent element, we set position to relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.60,0:07:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So in this case, that should be quite easy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.63,0:07:58.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is simply this product here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this article with the class of product.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.88,0:08:03.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, this is where now we want
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.22,0:08:08.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to set position to relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.59,0:08:12.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, now we can go back here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.83,0:08:17.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and say position absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.82,0:08:22.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And set the top and left to zero. Just to get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:26.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.82,0:08:31.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now we can kind of guess the values
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.13,0:08:32.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where this should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.42,0:08:36.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, let's say like minus 15 pixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.52,0:08:39.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That can be a little bit more, 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.15,0:08:41.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.98,0:08:44.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now it's like nicely in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.82,0:08:48.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and now let's move it also like 30 pixels to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.90,0:08:52.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's not quite centered yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.43,0:08:54.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say 35.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.43,0:08:57.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's actually make it 34,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:08:59.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so it's exactly double off the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.91,0:09:05.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right. So with this, we are almost done with this part.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.40,0:09:08.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All that's missing is this extra space
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:10.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,between the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.30,0:09:11.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.17,0:09:13.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So to give it this extra touch,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.39,0:09:16.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and also because I wanted you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.00,0:09:18.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to practice your Googling skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:21.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what I would have Googled is,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.04,0:09:26.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,CSS add space between characters,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.81,0:09:29.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or you could have written letters as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.22,0:09:34.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but here you actually immediately get the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.45,0:09:36.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So letters spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.33,0:09:38.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm more interested in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.29,0:09:40.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,usually in a stack overflow reply
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:44.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or this documentation of MDN.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:45.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So here we have letter spacing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:48.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which looks like something we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.89,0:09:51.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so here, indeed we get as always
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:53.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a couple of different examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.95,0:09:58.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, yeah. This is the property that we're gonna use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.04,0:09:59.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm copying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:03.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put it here, close to these styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.80,0:10:06.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm setting it to two pixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.81,0:10:11.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And yeah. That actually looks a lot nicer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.77,0:10:14.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just need to like, push it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.60,0:10:19.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,even a bit more to the side there, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.84,0:10:23.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To center it. And yeah, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.77,0:10:25.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we are done with this part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:29.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now let's quickly add those colors here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.12,0:10:33.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And as I said, previously, we will basically create a div.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:36.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So a container without any semantic meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.86,0:10:39.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then in there, I will create six more divs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:43.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then each of them will get its own background color.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:50.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, that should be right here after the link.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.55,0:10:57.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right? So after the link and before these product details.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.89,0:11:03.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So a div, and I'm calling it the colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.49,0:11:10.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just immediately close it so we don't forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:16.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because this editor is not as good as VS Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.24,0:11:18.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still quite helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:21.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to actually use CodePen for something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:25.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now we will just create another div in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.55,0:11:28.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.01,0:11:33.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then actually this doesn't have any content at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.74,0:11:36.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.41,0:11:40.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So this is something we didn't really do before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:47.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so let me just explain and show you how we will do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.40,0:11:48.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we want six colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:51.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm just a copy pasting it six times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.45,0:11:54.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:11:58.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put that right here at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.54,0:12:01.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So just like in the HTML.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:05.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the colors class is not really important, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:10.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's just start by defining each of the squares.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.56,0:12:12.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So each of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:15.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So basically we make them a square
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:18.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by giving them a certain height and then a width
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.73,0:12:19.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.24,0:12:24.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let me show that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.89,0:12:25.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The first thing we should do is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.99,0:12:27.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to give them a background color
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:30.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to make it easier to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.50,0:12:34.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The first one I think was black.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.13,0:12:39.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:40.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But right now they are not visible
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:42.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because they don't have any content.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we give them a height and the width,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.07,0:12:48.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then they will become visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:52.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's do that. Height 22 pixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:54.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so now immediately they get a height
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.57,0:12:57.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then they occupy all the space that they can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.90,0:13:02.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because they are block level elements by default, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:04.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So they are divs and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:06.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that is by default a block level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.67,0:13:11.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now if we specify their width to be the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.40,0:13:14.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so it looks like a square then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:18.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well then of course they no longer do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.73,0:13:19.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.56,0:13:23.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So of course we are still far away from the final result.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:26.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to continue effectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:29.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,let's now give each of them a different color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:32.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how can we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.10,0:13:35.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I will actually add another class to each of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.76,0:13:37.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that is completely possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.89,0:13:39.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that we are allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.81,0:13:42.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to give each element more than one class.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.87,0:13:44.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I showed you that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.82,0:13:47.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the way we do that, is to add a space
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:49.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then simply add another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.13,0:13:53.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So the first one was black,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:56.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then blue, red, yellow, green, and brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:13:58.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:01.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in the first one, we actually don't need to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:04.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because they are black already, all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.16,0:14:06.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so we can then basically override that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.98,0:14:08.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in all the other ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:13.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's call this one, the color blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:18.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then let me just copy-paste that a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.47,0:14:25.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So red,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:28.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,yellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:31.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,green,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.35,0:14:32.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:33.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:36.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now we will of course have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.01,0:14:38.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to select all of them right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:50.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So again, you could have come up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:53.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,with any blue color that you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:56.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My choice was this one, 2f6ee2.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.47,0:15:03.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.13,0:15:06.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And indeed, now it is blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:09.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we'll just copy this a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.62,0:15:13.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:15.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So red,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.34,0:15:18.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,yellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:19.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,green,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:22.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:27.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So not here, but here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.66,0:15:35.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here let's use the same red that I had before, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.84,0:15:40.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then the yellow was f0ef1e.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.05,0:15:48.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Green is 90cc20.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.91,0:15:53.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And finally the brown is 885214.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.63,0:15:57.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.95,0:16:00.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There we have all six different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.62,0:16:03.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, all we need to do is to put them side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:06.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how can we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.96,0:16:11.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there is a neat trick that we learned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.22,0:16:13.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is to change the display property
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.73,0:16:16.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of these elements to inline block.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.30,0:16:23.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we will now set all of these six elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:26.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So all of them, which have the class of color
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.70,0:16:29.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to inline block.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:32.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because like this, they will only occupy the space
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.62,0:16:34.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that they need and they will also
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.98,0:16:38.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,not create any line breaks after them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:40.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so that is exactly what we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.83,0:16:42.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now we could not use inline because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:46.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then the height and width wouldn't really work as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.29,0:16:49.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or at least they shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.35,0:16:52.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you see that indeed it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.83,0:16:54.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it needs to be inline block
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.41,0:16:56.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because remember height and width,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:16:58.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,do not apply to inline elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:02.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now all we need is a small margin
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:04.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to the right of each of them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.40,0:17:08.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of let's say, 12 pixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.12,0:17:10.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:14.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit too much, maybe. So 10 pixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.50,0:17:16.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.32,0:17:18.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's all we need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.52,0:17:20.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually we are missing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.37,0:17:24.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,like some space here after this anchor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:25.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And remember how we actually
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:27.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,already had this problem before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.78,0:17:29.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we tried to add some space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.84,0:17:33.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So some margin bottom to this anchor, but it didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:36.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so the work around was to then add that space
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:39.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at the top of this heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.96,0:17:41.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.35,0:17:45.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why here these details title, has the margin top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.21,0:17:47.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And by the time we didn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.47,0:17:52.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,why adding margin bottom to this anchor element didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:54.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now we actually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:56.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's do that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:01.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:06.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So let's add a margin bottom here of 30 pixels,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.50,0:18:08.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which will still not work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:11.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But again, we now know why it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:13.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the reason is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.74,0:18:16.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the anchor element is an inline element.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:18.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And on inline elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.38,0:18:22.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the top and margin bottoms do not apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.02,0:18:24.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, to fix that once again,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.26,0:18:28.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we need to display this as an inline block.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.09,0:18:30.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, easy enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.14,0:18:34.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Display inline block,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.54,0:18:37.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.28,0:18:40.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There we have, our 30 pixels now nicely displayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:43.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.55,0:18:45.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I think with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:51.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,our solution looks exactly the same as our demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.03,0:18:54.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we are done now as it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:18:59.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. So, it seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:01.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.08,0:19:06.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's actually a wraps up this introduction to CSS section.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.32,0:19:08.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So one more time, congratulations
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.98,0:19:12.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for reaching this first part of the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:16.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you now have all the fundamentals of HTML and CSS
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:19.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that you need in order to start building layouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.77,0:19:24.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which is actually one of the main parts of CSS.
